The Kruger National Park announced on its Twitter page that a guest was seriously injured after he dived into the pool at Shingwedzi Rest Camp today. The park said, “He has been rushed to hospital in Phalaborwa for medical attention. ALSO READ: No updates on missing KNP ranger as yet “Guests are reminded to follow the rules and regulations of every pool in the camps, which clearly states that people should not dive into pools. “We would like to wish the guest a speedy recovery.” This is a developing story.